      • getDataSourceTimestamp

        public long getDataSourceTimestamp(CmsRequest<G> request)
        Description copied from interface: Generator
        Get the latest timestamp of the data being used to generate the content. The timestamp should be for the content being generated by the generator. The timestamp should not represent data from other elements in the process chain with the exception of delegates not processed by CMS. This method is guaranteed to be called for every CMS (http / servlet) request.
        Specified by:
        getDataSourceTimestamp in interface Generator<G extends ContentElement>
        Parameters:
        request - the request.
        Returns:
        the timestamp or -1 if unknown.

      • getIdentity

        public String getIdentity(CmsRequest<G> request)
        Description copied from interface: Cacheable
        Return a string that uniquely identifies the information needed to generate or influence the content for the response.

        For example, if the response is dependent on a record from the database, an implementor should return a String representing the database key and a timestamp for when the record was last updated.
